Rules for Constructor: 
1. Class name & constructor name must be same.
2. Constructor does not return any value, bec it does not call by any method it automatically call's
when object created.
3. Modifiers used with constructor: public, default, private and protected.
4. Constructor can't be inherited but child class constructor can call parent class construtor by using super().
 
Default Constructor: 
1. Every class (user defined & pre-define) must have at least one constructor.
Compiler will create a default constructor.
2. In case of deafult constructor the modifier usef with constructor is same as with the class.
3. In default constructor super() line is present by default.

